      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If no input sources or timers are attached to the run loop, this method exits immediately; otherwise, it runs the receiver in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSDefaultRunLoopMode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " by repeatedly invoking "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsrunloop/1411525-runmode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". In other words, this method effectively begins an infinite loop that processes data from the run loopâ€™s input sources and timers. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Manually removing all known input sources and timers from the run loop is not a guarantee that the run loop will exit. macOS can install and remove additional input sources as needed to process requests targeted at the receiverâ€™s thread. Those sources could therefore prevent the run loop from exiting. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you want the run loop to terminate, you shouldn't use this method. Instead, use one of the other run methods and also check other arbitrary conditions of your own, in a loop. A simple example would be:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "BOOL shouldKeepRunning = YES; // global",
            "NSRunLoop *theRL = [NSRunLoop currentRunLoop];",
            "while (shouldKeepRunning && [theRL runMode:NSDefaultRunLoopMode beforeDate:[NSDate distantFuture]]);"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2555798",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "shouldKeepRunning"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " somewhere else in the program."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
